Caesar STANSEL, Jr., Defendant-Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee. No. 30567

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 30, 1971. R. P. Herndon, Atlanta, Ga., for defendant-appellant. John W. Stokes, Jr., U. S. Atty., Robert L. Smith, Asst. U. S. Atty., Atlanta, Ga., for plaintiff-appellee.

Before JOHN R. BROWN, Chief Judge, and INGRAHAM and RONEY, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir. See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5th Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5 Cir. 1970, 430 F.2d 966.
